'''José Antonio Acosta''' (18th century) was a Spanish Catholic priest, of outstanding performance during the Viceroyalty of Peru, serving in the holy charity of Buenos Aires.<ref>{{Citation |last= |first= |year= |title=Historia del protomedicato de Buenos Aires:|publisher=El Ateneo, 1937|publication-place= |page= |url=https://books.google.com.ar/books?id=KFBYAAAAMAAJ&q=jose+antonio+acosta+presbitero+buenos+aires&dq=jose+antonio+acosta+presbitero+buenos+aires&hl=es-419&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiFou2lxO7VAhXJnJAKHTs0BPQ4ChDoAQhFMAc|accessdate= }}</ref> He also served as Rector of the [[Colegio Nacional de Buenos Aires|Real Colegio de San Carlos]] between 1786 and 1792.<ref>{{Citation |last= |first= |year= |title=Documentos para la historia Argentina, Volume 18|publisher=Compañía Sud-Americana de Billetes de Banco|publication-place= |page= |url=https://books.google.com.ar/books?id=FqwfAQAAMAAJ&q=Jos%C3%A9+Antonio+Acosta+real+colegio+de+san+carlos&dq=Jos%C3%A9+Antonio+Acosta+real+colegio+de+san+carlos&hl=es-419&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiqrtf3xe7VAhVBHZAKHU2rA74Q6AEIJDAA|accessdate= }}</ref>
== Biography ==
Acosta was born in Buenos Aires, son of a Creole family of Portuguese and Spanish origin. He studied at the prestigious [[Colegio Nacional de Monserrat|Colegio of Monserrat]] located in [[Córdoba, Argentina|Córdoba]].<ref>{{Citation |last= |first= |year= |title=Finanzas, saberes y vida cotidiana en el Colegio Monserrat:|publisher=Universidad Nacional de Córdoba|publication-place= |page= |url=https://books.google.com.ar/books?id=i7xQAAAAMAAJ&q=jose+antonio+acosta+colegio+monserrat+cordoba&dq=jose+antonio+acosta+colegio+monserrat+cordoba&hl=es-419&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiQ3rCP3-7VAhXBj5AKHa0MDfsQ6AEIJDAA|accessdate= }}</ref> And he probably did his tertiary studies in [[University of Saint Francis Xavier]].
Acosta was an active defender of the rights of the underprivileged. In 1775, he denounced before the viceregal authorities, the abuses committed by the [[Encomienda|encomendero]] of the tribes of the [[Itatí, Corrientes]].<ref>{{Citation |last= |first= |year= |title=Patrimonio artístico nacional:|publisher=Iris Gori, Sergio Barbieri, Academia Nacional de Bellas Artes (Argentina)|publication-place= |page= |url=https://books.google.com.ar/books?id=_uBBAQAAIAAJ&q=jose+antonio+acosta+cura+buenos+aires&dq=jose+antonio+acosta+cura+buenos+aires&hl=es-419&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiF1ZbMze7VAhUIH5AKHcjQC-EQ6AEIMzAD|accessdate= }}</ref> In 1790 Acosta served as an interim chaplain in [[Puerto Deseado]] (Patagonia).<ref>{{Citation |last= |first= |year= |title=Archivum: revista de la Junta de Historia Eclesiástica Argentina, Volumes 10-11|publisher=Argentina|publication-place= |page= |url=https://books.google.com.ar/books?id=VpdXAAAAMAAJ&q=jose+antonio+acosta+presbitero+buenos+aires&dq=jose+antonio+acosta+presbitero+buenos+aires&hl=es-419&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjawezBy-7VAhVJkZAKHYZjA_0Q6AEIOzAF|accessdate= }}</ref> He also had outstanding acting as a teacher, serving in several periods as rector of the main College of Buenos Aires.<ref>{{Citation |last= |first= |year= |title=Colegio Real de San Carlos:|publisher=Armando de Sousa Argüello|publication-place= |page= |url=https://books.google.com.ar/books?id=qKRBAAAAYAAJ&q=jose+antonio+acosta+rector+buenos+aires&dq=jose+antonio+acosta+rector+buenos+aires&hl=es-419&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwij0ai01-7VAhVFvZAKHTqUBrQQ6AEIKDAB|accessdate= }}</ref>
As a priest of the Cathedral of Buenos Aires, José Antonio Acosta realized the marriages and baptism of distinguished personalities of Buenos Aires, including the marriage of [[Patricio French|Patricio French de Alcala]] and Bernardina Manuela Dávila de Lafuente.<ref>{{Citation |last= |first= |year= |title=San Telmo: su pasado histórico|publisher=Ediciones República de San Telmo|publication-place= |page= |url=https://books.google.com.ar/books?id=S6lXAAAAMAAJ&q=jose+antonio+acosta+catedral+de+buenos+aires&dq=jose+antonio+acosta+catedral+de+buenos+aires&hl=es-419&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiM2-L4ze7VAhUBfpAKHW5yApIQ6AEIMjAD|accessdate= }}</ref> He was the priest who had blessed to [[Juan Gregorio de las Heras]],<ref>{{Citation |last= |first= |year= |title=Notas biográficas publicadas en la sección Efemérides americanas de "La Nación":|publisher=José Arturo Scotto|publication-place= |page= |url=https://books.google.com.ar/books?id=9D66i8UIExYC&q=jose+antonio+acosta+gregorio+las+heras+buenos+aires&dq=jose+antonio+acosta+gregorio+las+heras+buenos+aires&hl=es-419&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiF1byD5-7VAhWLPpAKHYJvBjgQ6AEIJDAA|accessdate= }}</ref> and Maria Josefa Anastacia Belgrano González, daughter of [[Domingo Belgrano]] and María Josefa González.<ref>{{Citation |last= |first= |year= |title=Bautismos 1752-1775|publisher=Nuestra Señora de La Merced|publication-place= |page= |url=https://www.familysearch.org/ark:/61903/3:1:9396-XTS3-NF?i=426&cc=1974184|accessdate= }}</ref> He also baptized several members of the [[Domingo de Basavilbaso|Basavilbaso]] family, one of the most important families of the city.<ref>{{Citation |last= |first= |year= |title=Crónicas y linajes de la gobernación del Plata:|publisher=Luis Enrique Azarola Gil|publication-place= |page= |url=https://books.google.com.ar/books?id=YopoAAAAMAAJ&q=jose+antonio+acosta+catedral+de+buenos+aires&dq=jose+antonio+acosta+catedral+de+buenos+aires&hl=es-419&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjr0P2Nw-7VAhVChpAKHbc1DL8Q6AEISTAJ|accessdate= }}</ref>
