'''Masnat''' is a piece of [[Islamic embroidery|embroidered]] [[velvet]] cloth used by Royals of [[Mughal Empire|Mughal]], [[Qutb Shahi]], [[Asaf Jahi]]s etc. It is also used during Muslim weddings.<ref>{{cite news |title= Masnat makers on the moribund|author= Syed Mohammad|url= http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-01-30/hyderabad/31005496_1_hyderabadis-gold-and-silver-weddings|newspaper= Times of India|date= |accessdate=31 January 2012}}</ref> It is hand woven with shimmering zari on a velvet cloth. The rulers use to proclaim their orders sitting on a masnat.

